The Director-General of the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC), Major General Shuaibu Ibrahim has commiserated with the Oyo State government and the people of Ogbomosho over the death of His Royal Majesty, Oba Jimoh Oladunni Oyewumi Ajagungbade III. Speaking at Soun’s palace on Saturday, the Director-General consoles the entire town especially the immediate family on the death of the revered monarch and prayed for the repose of his soul. The DG, in a statement signed byEmeka Mgbemena, Deputy Director, Press and Public Relations said,“On behalf of the NYSC family nationwide, please accept our heartfelt condolences.” Army Releases Female Soldier Detained For Accepting Corp Member… DG Flags Off 2021 NYSC SAED Festival The Scheme had earlier written to the Oyo State Government, Minister of Youth and Sports Development and the family of the deceased monarch to express condolences on the demise of the monarch. In his response, the eldest son of the monarch, Dr Aderemi Oyewumi commended the Director-General for creating time for the visit. He lauded NYSC Management for mentoring youths as models for good governance, describing the Scheme as an agent of national unity. He poured encomiums on the founding father of the Scheme, General Yakubu Gowon for the establishment of the Corps which in forty-eight years has continued to promote national unity and integration. On hand to receive the Director-General was a member of the NYSC National Governing Board, Prince Oyekunle Oyewumi, who is also a son of the deceased monarch, High Chief Samuel Sobalaje Otolorin, the Are-Ago of Ogbomosoland, and High Chief Yusuf Kasali Oladipo, the Abese of Ogbomosoland, among others.